Quote: Drag the  chain, to.-To be the slowest shearer in a shed.
Notes: (Acland Gloss.)

Date: 0/0/1941
Source: NZ Slang
Author: BAKER
Vol / Page: 39
Edition:
Quote: From the New Zealand shearing sheds came those effective expressions  to drag the chain and swing the gate, phrases applied to the slowest and the fastest shearer in the shed respectively.
Notes:

